The paper deals with salient object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training a convolutional neural network-based image classifier, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of bottom-up saliency approaches, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) applications.
